04/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The opposition Serbian Progressive Party (SNS) still plans to hold a large-scale anti-government rally on April 16th in Belgrade, SNS official Marko Djuric said on Sunday (April 3rd). 
He added that the party has no invitation yet from the ruling coalition for talks about possible early elections. 
Djuric also announced that the SNS will hold an anti-government rally in Leskovac on April 9th. 
(Tanjug, RTS - 03/04/11)
